comments:
That part which until 1.4.1934 formed parts of the parishes of 
    East Donyland, Langenhoe, Stanway, West Bergholt and Wivenhoe. See also Table 2, note 
    (m).

That part which until 14.10.1938 formed part of the parish of Dedham. See 
    also Table 2, note (j).

That part which until 1.4.1934 formed part of the parish of 
    Inworth. See also Table 2, note (l).

Abolished 1.4.1934 and divided between the parishes of Tiptree, 
    Feering and Messing cum Inwortrh. See also Table 2, notes (b) and (l).

Created 1.4.1934 out of the separate parishes of Messing and Inworth. 
    See also Table 2, note (m).

Created 1.4.1934 out of the parishes of Tolleshunt Knights, Inworth, 
    Messing, tolleshunt D'Arcy. See also Table 2, note (m).
